strings : repeat

Write a method named repeat that accepts a string and a number of repetitions as parameters and returns the string concatenated that many times. For example, the call of repeat("hello", 3) returns "hellohellohello". 
If the number of repetitions is 0 or less, return an empty string.



 public static String repeat(String str, int numberOfReps) {
        String str2 = "";
        for(int i = 0; i < numberOfReps; i++) {
            str2 += str;
        }
        return str2;
    }
